One Decision to Make Now
[Likely] You need to decide: where does the APK actually live?
Option A — local filesystem (what I described above): simplest, works for dev and demo, breaks if you ever run multiple instances or the disk fills up.
Option B — cloud storage (S3/MinIO): the production-correct choice, but adds AWS SDK dependency and complexity you don't need right now.
