One Thing to Nail Down Before You Write a Line of Code
Your StorageService.store() returns a relative path that gets saved in app_versions.file_path. The relative path format you choose right now is permanent — changing it later means a DB migration to update all existing paths.
Decide this now and stick to it:
/{appId}/{versionTag}/{uuid}_{originalFilename}
Example:
/42/1.0.0/a3f9c2d1-calculator-pro.apk
Absolute path on disk = baseUploadPath + relativePath:
/var/applivo/uploads/42/1.0.0/a3f9c2d1-calculator-pro.apk
This is the format I'd recommend. App-scoped directories mean cleanup is rm -rf uploads/42/ when an app is deleted — no scattered files to hunt down.

