The One Edge Case Most People Miss
When uploadVersion() succeeds writing to disk but the DB save throws — you have an orphaned APK file with no DB record pointing to it. Your @Transactional won't help here because the file write happened outside the transaction boundary.
Handle it explicitly in VersionService.uploadVersion():
try:
    store file → get path
    save AppVersion entity with path
except (any exception after file write):
    storageService.delete(path)  ← cleanup orphan
    rethrow
This is the kind of production thinking that makes an interviewer lean forward. Put it in your README too.